# Final pass verification (Designed by Anthony)

This repo is an **Astro** site deployed to **Vercel**. Interactive features talk to a separate **Lighthouse audit API** via `PUBLIC_API_URL` (see merge workflow env and `AuditForm.astro`, `LighthouseAudit.astro`, `src/pages/report/index.astro`).

## Commands to run before merging / going live

- **`npm run test:release`** ‚Äî `test:api` (external Lighthouse API only) then **`test:e2e`**, which starts **`astro preview` at `http://127.0.0.1:4321`** after a fresh `npm run build`. Full E2E is always against the **current repo**, not the live site (production may still use older cookie/analytics markup).
- **Static parity headers (production-like CSP):** **`npm run test:e2e:hosting`** ‚Äî uses **`playwright.hosting.config.ts`** to serve `dist/` via **`node scripts/static-parity-server.mjs`** at **`http://127.0.0.1:5500`** (see **`static-headers.json`**), so **`static-headers.json` CSP, HSTS, Trusted Types, etc.** apply. **`npm run test:security-headers`** runs only project **`5-hosting`** (security + console checks). **`npm run test:release:hosting`** = API check + full E2E on the parity server. **`node scripts/playwright-hosting.mjs`** is still available as a cross-platform wrapper around the same config.
- **Live-only checks:** `npm run test:smoke:live` / `npm run test:seo:live` use `BASE_URL=https://designedbyanthony.com` and skip the local preview server.
- Lighter options: `npm run test:smoke` (only `smoke.spec.ts`), or `npm run test:e2e` alone if you already built.

1. `npm ci`
2. `npm run build` ‚Äî must succeed (same as CI).
3. `npm run test:smoke` ‚Äî quick core pages and forms (only if you want a fast check).
4. `npm run test:api` ‚Äî hosted API responds.
5. `npm run test:e2e` ‚Äî **full** suite (all of `e2e/`), not just smoke.
6. Before go-live on **header / CSP** changes: `npm run test:security-headers`, `npm run test:e2e:hosting`, or `test:release:hosting`.

### CSP / ‚Äúmax protection‚Äù strategy (realistic order)

- **Do not** try to get Lighthouse ‚Äúperfect‚Äù and a **clear console** in one step while **GTM + Turnstile + Sentry** run ‚Äî third parties will always add noise. Prefer: **Sentry CSP reports** + **`Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only`** in `build/csp.mjs` ‚Üí fix violations ‚Üí then tighten **enforcing** `DIRECTIVES` in `build/csp.mjs` and `pnpm run sync:static-headers`.
- **Playwright:** `e2e/console-hosting.spec.ts` (parity server only) fails on **uncaught page errors** and **console errors** (with a small **allowlist** in `e2e/console-allowlist.ts`). It **declines** analytics so GTM stays off; tighten the allowlist as you remove noise.
- `npm run test:e2e` uses **astro preview** (no edge headers). **`npm run test:e2e:hosting`** uses the **static parity server** so CSP matches production.

## API integration map

- **Contact / lead forms**: `POST` `{PUBLIC_API_URL}/api/contact` (client-side; Turnstile blocks unattended submits in E2E).
- **SEO audit**: `POST` `{PUBLIC_API_URL}/api/audit`.
- **Report viewer** (`/report/...`): `GET` `{PUBLIC_API_URL}/api/report/:id`.

## Automation on GitHub

- **CI** (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`): on every PR and on `main` pushes, runs `npm run test:api` so the Lighthouse API must respond before merges are trusted. Uses `PLAYWRIGHT_SKIP_BROWSER_DOWNLOAD=1` (request-only test; no browser install).
- **Cursor Bugbot** (if enabled for this repo in Cursor): reviews PRs for defects separately from CI. CI proves the API wire is live; Bugbot helps catch logic and quality issues. They complement each other.

## Agent checklist

- If changing env or API URLs, update **GitHub Actions** `PUBLIC_API_URL` in **ci.yml** plus any docs that mention the default host.
- After UI changes to forms or report pages, run smoke + API tests; manually exercise one real submit in staging or production if behavior is critical.
